# ============================================================
# Krishi Drishti — Environment Variables (.env)
# ============================================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your credentials:
#   cp .env.example .env
# Then edit .env with your real API keys.
#
# All services below are FREE to register. No payment needed.
# ============================================================

# ========== 1. CDSE (Copernicus Data Space Ecosystem) ==========
# FREE registration: https://dataspace.copernicus.eu
# After login → User Settings → OAuth Clients → Create
# REQUIRED for real Sentinel-2 and Sentinel-1 satellite data.
CDSE_CLIENT_ID=your_cdse_client_id_here
CDSE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_cdse_client_secret_here

# ========== 2. Google Earth Engine (GEE) ==========
# FREE registration: https://signup.earthengine.google.com
# Then create a Cloud Project: https://console.cloud.google.com
# Enable Earth Engine API, create Service Account, download JSON key.
#
# Option A: Service Account (recommended for servers)
# Download JSON key file and set the path below:
GEE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=/path/to/your-service-account-key.json
#
# Option B: Local auth (for development)
# Run: earthengine authenticate
# Then leave GEE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON empty — it uses your local credentials.

# ========== 3. Supabase (PostgreSQL Database) ==========
# FREE registration: https://supabase.com
# Create a project → Settings → API → copy Project URL and API keys.
# Use "anon public" key (or new "Publishable" key sb_publishable_xxx).
# Then run supabase_migration.sql in Supabase SQL Editor.
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_KEY=your_supabase_publishable_or_anon_key_here

# ========== 4. USGS / NASA (Optional) ==========
# FREE registration: https://ers.cr.usgs.gov (USGS)
# FREE registration: https://urs.earthdata.nasa.gov (NASA Earthdata)
# Only needed for direct Landsat/USGS data (GEE is preferred).
USGS_USERNAME=your_usgs_username
USGS_PASSWORD=your_usgs_password
NASA_EARTHDATA_USER=your_nasa_earthdata_user
NASA_EARTHDATA_PASS=your_nasa_earthdata_pass

# ========== 5. ISRO Bhoonidhi (Optional) ==========
# FREE for Indian citizens: https://bhuvan.nrsc.gov.in
# For ISRO satellite data (Resourcesat, Cartosat, RISAT, HySIS).
BHOONIDHI_USER=your_bhoonidhi_username
BHOONIDHI_PASS=your_bhoonidhi_password

# ========== 6. IBM Quantum (Optional) ==========
# FREE tier: 10 min/month on real hardware
# Registration: https://quantum.ibm.com → Get API token
# Simulators work WITHOUT this token (unlimited, free).
IBM_QUANTUM_TOKEN=your_ibm_quantum_token_here

# ============================================================
# NOTES:
# - NASA POWER and Open-Meteo weather APIs work WITHOUT any key
# - Sentinel-2 CDSE gives you 10m resolution real vegetation indices
# - GEE gives you 10+ additional datasets (Landsat, SMAP, GRACE, DEM, etc.)
# - Without credentials: app uses simulated/demo data (still functional)
# - With credentials: app uses REAL satellite data for your location
# ============================================================
